## Create Network Rule

### Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| **Database** | `{{ rule_db | upper }}` |
| **Schema** | `{{ rule_schema | upper }}` |
| **Rule Name** | `{{ rule_db | upper }}.{{ rule_schema | upper }}.JIRA_NETWORK_RULE` |
| **Type** | HOST_PORT / EGRESS |

### Allowed Hosts

| Host | Port | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| `snowflakecomputing.atlassian.net` | 443 | Resolves Jira Cloud ID from instance URL |
| `api.atlassian.com` | 443 | All Jira REST API calls |

> **Both hosts are required.** The connector first contacts the instance URL to resolve the Atlassian Cloud ID, then routes all subsequent API calls through `api.atlassian.com`. Omitting either host will cause the `Jira Connection` controller to fail validation.
